WorldStage NewsOnline— Following unending killing and kidnapping of christians in Nigeria, the General Overseer of The Redeemed Christian Church of God, Pastor Enoch Adeboye on Sunday led  members of the church on a prayer walk and protest across the country. The protest  started around 10 a.m. and the general overseer, as well as other leaders of the church joined the procession from the church’s national headquarters in Ebute-Meta, Lagos State. Members of the church also joined the protest in their local churches nationwide. In Lagos, RCCG members were seen in Ogba,  Fagba, Ikeja and other locations caring placards and banners, asking  President Muhammadu Buhari to end the killings in the country. Adeboye had directed all members of the church to participate in the prayer and fasting programme as well as the prayer walk declared by the Christian Association of Nigeria to address a spate of killings across the country.